ling a lawsuit against an outofstate corporation that owns retail locations in california i was instructed to serve its agent for service but the company does not have one how can i properly serve the business  and is it legal for it to continue doing business in california without having an agent can our nonprofit get in trouble for failing to file tax returns we live in a townhouse run by a nonprofit association Â the ccrs say that Â the association is a nonprofit organization do we need to file taxes yearly our extreasurer did not file for the past two years i think we might be in trouble are we can my corporate directors be hb visa holders in california the home state of the questioner the law places no restrictions on who may be directors i want to sell but the other shareholder doesnt who wins a friend and i formed a corporation together and we share ownership equally the business is in financial trouble now and i would like to sell it and make at least something out of it before it is too late my partner says she cannot afford to buy me out and refuses to sell what should i do should my very small business incorporate in delaware i have heard that delaware has the most businessfriendly corporation laws would i save money or gain other benefits if i incorporated my new twoowner business in delaware or is it better to do so in my own state related products more form your own limited liability company llc or corporation nolos guide to singlemember llcs nolos quick llc more legal topics professional corporations s corporations more legal topics professional corporations s corporations related ads need professional help  talk to a business law attorney zip code start how it works briefly tell us about your case provide your contact information choose attorneys to contact you copyright   nolo Â® selfhelp services may not be permitted in all states the information provided on this site is not legal advice does not constitute a lawyer referral service and no attorney