ne of these seven types of companies and partnerships refers to llps like many other countries two persons are required to form an llp in iran each person has hisher own shares and is responsible for business liability equivalent to hisher share percentage llps in iran are named according to the format illustrated by the following example sherkat ba masooliyate mahdood translates as sherkat Ø´Ø±Ú©Øª company  mahdood ÙØ­Ø¯ÙØ¯ limited  masooliyat ÙØ³Ø¦ÙÙÛØª liability italyedit the italian civil code approved in  and as amended by the government act  and furthers modifications mainly provides three forms of limited liability company societÃ  per azioni spa the minimum required starting capital for an spa is â¬ the capital is divided into shares azioni that can be transferred by endorsement or bought and sold on stock exchange only spas can be quoted in stock exchange market issue corporate bonds and other financial instruments spa form and a higher capital are required by law to operate in protected businesses ie banks leasing companies etc societÃ  a responsabilitÃ  limitata srl the minimum required starting capital for an srl is â¬ its capital is divided into stakes quote which can be bought or sold just by notarial act srls can issue corporate bonds but are subject to many limitations similar to the srl is the societÃ  cooperativa a responsabilitÃ  limitata scarl whose scope is not making profit but give benefits to stakes holders societÃ  in accomandita per azioni sapa the minimum required starting capital for a sapa is â¬ divided into shares sapas have a mixed liability scheme where standard shareholders have limited liability while managing shareholders have full liability except this sapas are exactly like spas even if uncommon companies append the corresponding abbreviation to their company names japanedit japan passed legislation in  creating a new type of business organization godo kaisha jllc a close variant of the american llccitation needed japane