pation in the form of capital of professional contribution or of any combination of both empresa individual de responsabilidad limitada eirl a legal entity with one single owner the capital for any of the above entities is freely determined by its statutes there is no minimum requirement except for entities with certain types of activities mainly in the financial markets and then irrespective of their type polandedit in poland a limited liability company is referred to literally as âcompany with limited liabilityâ spÃ³Åka z ograniczonÄ odpowiedzialnoÅciÄ legally abbreviated as sp z oo or sometimes sp z oo in particular names informally in the polish speaking slang it is abbreviated as spÃ³Åka zoo pronounced with a long o as in tow however sp z oo has a separate from its owners legal personality which gives it the ability to do certain actions under law and it is considered a corporation the minimum start capital is  pln since  until then  pln portugaledit in portugal llcs are called sociedades de responsabilidade limitada that is company of limited responsibility usually abbreviated lda they are tax subject and company shares cannot be sold in a public market since  the transference of them is not required to be done in the presence of a civil law notary except if the company owns buildings in the same way other major properties have to be sold nonetheless the responsibility of the partners is limited to the capital share they hold and the minimum capital required by law for a lda of â¬ in  the ps government led by josÃ© socrates did reduce the minimum capital to â¬ but in  the new psd government led by pedro passos coelho reinstated the â¬ minimum capital the capital is not required to be deposited at the time of the registration of the company instead the share holders have until  december of the year the registry was madecitation needed romaniaedit romania recognizes the limited liability company since  under the name of societate cu rÄspundere limit